The paper deals with the problem of learning representations of entities and relations in knowledge graphs for predicting missing links, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves modeling and inferring various relation patterns, which is a topic of interest in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of negative sampling for training the model, which is a common technique in database systems (cs.DB).
